Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js App Router

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in package.json
- Generated package-lock.json updated with new dependencies

### 2. Component Integration
- Modified: `src/app/layout.jsx`
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag (after the UserProvider closing tag)
  - This follows Next.js App Router best practices for Next.js v13.5+ as specified in the official documentation

### 3. Framework-Specific Implementation
- Used Next.js-specific import path: `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Placed component in the root layout to ensure it's included across all pages
- No additional configuration required for basic setup

## Verification Steps Completed
✓ Package installation successful (npm install)
✓ Build completed successfully with no errors (npm run build)
✓ All routes compiled correctly
✓ TypeScript validation passed
✓ Lock file updated (package-lock.json)

## Next Steps for Deployment
To complete the Speed Insights setup:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard:
   - Navigate to your project in Vercel
   - Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
   - Click "Enable" button
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. After deployment, Speed Insights will begin collecting performance metrics
4. View insights in the Vercel dashboard after users visit the site

## Technical Notes
- The SpeedInsights component is lightweight and won't impact page performance
- It automatically tracks Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.)
- The component is rendered on the client side only
- No environment variables or additional configuration required for basic functionality
- Compatible with the existing Next.js 16.0.7 setup and React 19.2.1
